CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 1, 1958, pg. A19, reads: "Well Done! - Honor stars were before the names of these 15 students on the commencement program at Westinghouse Hight School, last Friday. Recognized for their honor grades are, left to right: seated: Muriel Wilson, Dorothy Gloster, Audrey Lamar, Mildred Stewart and Winifred Haddock.  Standing: Patricia DeMauro, Antoinette Marsteller, Virginia Pegnato, Darlene Daniels, Vincent Paiano, Helen Pryor, Barbara Vaughn, Louise Nelson, Juanita Graves and Virginia Holmes. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Westinghouse High School honor student graduates, left to right seated: Muriel Wilson, Dorothy Gloster, Audrey Lamar, Mildred Stewart, and Winifred Haddock; standing: Patricia DeMauro, Antoinette Marsteller, Virginia Pegnato, Darlene Daniels, Vincent Paiano, Helen Pryor, Barbara Vaughn, Louise Nelson, Juanita Graves, and Virginia Holmes
